This paper is about analyzing activities and interactions in surveillance videos using unsupervised learning. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian Process (GP) and Hierarchical Dirichlet Process (HDP) models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, suggesting that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper deals with video data, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance videos and anomaly detection, which suggests that it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
